# RxJS to the rescue!
### 1. Observables
<ul><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;Building blocks of FRP in RxJS&lt;/div&gt;<br></li><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;First class objects to represent Asynchronous Data&lt;/div&gt;<br></li><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;Operators with fabulous Functional Grammar&lt;/div&gt;</li><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;Interoperable with other sync/async data&lt;/div&gt;</li></ul><div><br></div><div><div>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;</div><div>&lt;pre&gt;</div><div>&lt;i class=&quot;fa fa-lightbulb-o&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; An Observable is an event stream which can emit zero or more events, and may or may not finish.&#xA0;</div><div><br></div><div>If it finishes, then it does so by either emitting an error or&#xA0;</div><div>a special &#x201C;complete&#x201D; event.</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div><div>&lt;/div&gt;</div></div>
### 1. Arrays Are iterable
<div>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;<br></div><div>&lt;pre&gt;</div><div>&lt;code class=&quot;js&quot;&gt;</div><div>Array</div><div>&#xA0; .of(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)</div><div>&#xA0; .map(x =&gt; x * x)</div><div>&#xA0; .filter(x =&gt; x%2 === 0)</div><div>&#xA0; .reduce((x, acc) =&gt; x + acc)</div><div>&lt;/code&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div><div>&lt;/div&gt;</div>
### 2.Observables are iterables
<div>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;<br></div><div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div><div>&lt;code&gt;</div><div><div>Observable</div><div>&#xA0; .of(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)</div><div>&#xA0; .map(x =&gt; x * x)</div><div>&#xA0; .filter(x =&gt; x%2 === 0)</div><div>&#xA0; .reduce((x, acc) =&gt; x + acc)</div></div><div>&lt;/code&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div></div><div>&lt;/div&gt;</div><div><br></div><div><div>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;<br></div><div></div></div><div>&lt;pre&gt;</div><div>&lt;i class=&quot;fa fa-lightbulb-o&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Remember:</div><div>&#xA0;we return a new Observable every time we do any transformation</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;<br></div><div>&lt;/div&gt;</div>
### 3.Observables are lazy
<div>&lt;pre&gt;</div><div>&lt;code class=&quot;js&quot;&gt;</div><div>let users_ = getUsersObservable();</div><div><br></div><div>let notJohnConners_ =&#xA0;</div><div>&#xA0; users_</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; .map(user =&gt; user.fullName)</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; .map(name =&gt; name.first + &apos; &apos; + name.last)</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; .filter(x =&gt; x === &apos;John Connor&apos;);</div><div><br></div><div>notJohnConners_.subscribe(</div><div>&#xA0;(user) =&gt; console.log(&apos;New user arrived: &apos;, user),</div><div>&#xA0;(error) =&gt; console.log(&apos;Error Occured&apos;, error),</div><div>&#xA0;() =&gt; console.log(&apos;All Done&apos;)</div><div>)</div><div>&lt;/code&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div>
### 4.You can make anything into an observable
### 1.Arrays
<div><div>&lt;pre&gt;<br></div></div><div>&lt;code class=&quot;js&quot;&gt;</div><div>var a = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];</div><div>var a$ = Observable.from(a);</div><div>var b$ = Observable.of(1, 2, 3);</div><div>&lt;/code&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt; &#xA0; &#xA0;</div>
### 2.Promises
<div>&lt;pre&gt;<br></div><div><div>&lt;code class=&quot;js&quot;&gt;</div><div><div>var a = iPromiseOfSomething();</div><div>var a_ = Observable.fromPromise(a);</div></div><div>&lt;/code&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div></div>
### 3.Events
<div><div>&lt;pre class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;<br></div></div><div><div>&lt;code class=&quot;js&quot;&gt;</div><div><div>var result = document</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0;.getElementById(&apos;result&apos;);</div><div>var source =&#xA0;</div><div>Rx.Observable.fromEvent(result, &apos;click&apos;);</div></div><div><br></div><div>var observer = Rx.Observer.create(</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; function (x) {</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; console.log(&apos;Next: &apos; + x);</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; },</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; function (err) {</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; console.log(&apos;Error: &apos; + err);</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; },</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; function () {</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; console.log(&apos;Completed&apos;);</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; }</div><div>);</div><div>source.subscribe(observer)</div><div>&lt;/code&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div></div><div><div>&lt;pre class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;</div><div>&lt;i class=&quot;fa fa-lightbulb-o&quot;&gt;&lt;/i&gt; Rx will truncate multiple arguments from events,&#xA0;</div><div>you can use the selector function to combine all of them&lt;/b&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div></div>
### 4.Callbacks
<div>&lt;pre&gt;<br></div><div><div>&lt;code class=&quot;js&quot;&gt;</div></div><div>writeFile = require(&apos;fs&apos;).writeFile;</div><div><br></div><div>wf_ = Observable</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; &#xA0; .fromNodeCallback(writeFile);</div><div>&lt;/code&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div>
### 5.Custom Observables
<ul><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;Similar to resolve and reject in Promises&lt;/div&gt;</li><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;We can create custom observables&lt;/div&gt;</li><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;We have three functions: OnNext, OnComplete, OnError&lt;/div&gt;</li></ul><div>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;</div><div>&lt;pre&gt;<br></div><div>&lt;code class=&quot;js&quot;&gt;</div><div><div>var source = Rx.Observable.create(function (observer) {</div><div>&#xA0; observer.onNext(42);<br></div><div>&#xA0; observer.onCompleted();</div><div><br></div><div>&#xA0; return function () {<br></div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; console.log(&apos;disposed&apos;);</div><div>&#xA0; }</div><div>});</div><div>var subscription = source.subscribe(</div><div>&#xA0; function (x) { console.log(&apos;onNext: %s&apos;, x); },</div><div>&#xA0; function (e) { console.log(&apos;onError: %s&apos;, e); },</div><div>&#xA0; function () { console.log(&apos;onCompleted&apos;); });</div><div><br></div><div><div>subscription.dispose();</div></div></div><div>&lt;/code&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div><div>&lt;/div&gt;</div>
### 5. You can combine multiple Observables
<div><div>&lt;pre&gt;</div><div>&lt;code class=&quot;js&quot;&gt;</div></div><div>var api1 = &quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=query&amp;prop=extracts&amp;format=json&amp;exintro=&amp;titles=Stack%20Overflow&quot;;</div><div>var api2 = &quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=query&amp;prop=extracts&amp;format=json&amp;exintro=&amp;titles=Computer%20Science&quot;;</div><div><br></div><div>var promise1 = $.get(api1);</div><div>var promise2 = $.get(api2);</div><div><br></div><div>var source1 =&#xA0;</div><div>Rx.Observable.fromPromise(promise1);</div><div><br></div><div>var source2=&#xA0;</div><div>Rx.Observable.fromPromise(promise2);</div><div><br></div><div>var combined = Rx.Observable.concat(source1,source2);</div><div>&lt;/code&gt;</div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div>
# Reactive Programming
<ul><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;RxJS is Based on the observer and iterator patterns&lt;/div&gt;<br></li><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;Reactive can be explained as: &lt;/div&gt;<br></li><ul><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;Module Foo and Module Bar&lt;/div&gt;<br></li><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;Module Bar is said to be reactive when it listens to modules Foo&apos;s changes&lt;/div&gt;</li><li>&lt;div class=&quot;fragment&quot;&gt;Foo doesn&apos;t know that Bar exists!&lt;/div&gt;</li></ul></ul>

# Excercise
&lt;pre&gt;<div>&lt;code&gt;</div><div>test(&apos;querying over events&apos;, function () {</div><div>&#xA0; var results = 0;</div><div><br></div><div>&#xA0; var e = new EventEmitter();</div><div><br></div><div>&#xA0; Observable.fromEvent(e, &apos;click&apos;)</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; .filter(function (click) { return click.x === click.y })</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; .map(function (click) { return __ + __; })</div><div>&#xA0; &#xA0; .subscribe(function (x) { results = x; });</div><div><br></div><div>&#xA0; e.emit(&apos;click&apos;, {x: 100, y: 50});</div><div>&#xA0; e.emit(&apos;click&apos;, {x: 75, &#xA0;y: 75});</div><div>&#xA0; e.emit(&apos;click&apos;, {x: 40, &#xA0;y: 80});</div><div><br></div><div>&#xA0; equal(results, 150);</div><div><br></div><div>// fill in the __ inside map</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>});</div><div>&lt;/code&gt;<br></div><div><div><div>&lt;/pre&gt;</div></div></div>
